topic: History Workflow Series ("Ancient Civilization explorative search")

goals.1: Identify the BGP for Ancient Egypt
goals.2: Find the Ancient Egypt pharaohs born between 1500 BCE and 1000 BCE who had more than 8 child (the result set must be a list of triples pharaoh IRI,label and #children).
goals.3: Find all the ancient civilizations. Return the IRI and name of the civilization and also their duration (in number of years) if it is available.
goals.5: For each ancient civilization find the number of archeologists who worked on it (return also the civilizations with no archeologists) (the result set must be triples of civilization IRI, label and #archeologist).
goals.7: List all the twelve olympian greek deities (the result set must a list of 12 elements of couples of deity IRI and label).
goals.8: Compare ancient Greece with ancient Egypt and find how many deities each one has.

setup the file and create the empty json
find the properties of Meidum Pyramid

2.narrative:
insert the result of TASK 1 in the file
list the pharaoh's properties
output: said to be the same as

2.narrative: I have to find the children and date of birth
2.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?prop ?name WHERE { ?phar wdt:P39 wd:Q37110; ?prop ?x. ?prop sc:name ?name. FILTER(REGEX(?name,"[C,c]hild") || REGEX(?name,"[D,d]ate")). }

2.narrative: filter for pharaohs born between -1500 and -1000 and find who had more than 8 children
2.query: SELECT ?phar ?name COUNT(DISTINCT ?ch) AS ?children WHERE { ?phar wdt:P39 wd:Q37110; wdt:P569 ?x; wdt:P40 ?ch. FILTER(?x>xsd:datetime("-1500-01-01") && ?x<xsd:datetime("-1000-01-01") ). ?phar sc:name ?name. } GROUP BY ?phar ?name HAVING (COUNT(DISTINCT ?ch) > 8)

3.narrative: find the ancient civilizations possibily with their duration
3.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?obj ?o ?duration WHERE { ?obj wdt:P31 wd:Q28171280. OPTIONAL{ ?obj wdt:P580 ?start; wdt:P582 ?end. BIND(year(?end)-year(?start) AS ?duration). } ?obj sc:name ?o. }
output: history of ancient Israel and Judah

4.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?x ?o WHERE { ?obj wdt:P31 wd:Q28171280. ?x wdt:P101 ?obj. ?x sc:name ?o. } LIMIT 10
SELECT DISTINCT ?occ ?o WHERE { ?obj wdt:P31 wd:Q28171280. ?x wdt:P101 ?obj; wdt:P106 ?occ. ?occ sc:name ?o. }
SELECT wd:Q3621491 AS ?occ ?o WHERE { wd:Q3621491 sc:name ?o. }

5.narrative:
insert the result of TASK 1 in the file
find the number of archologists for each ancient civilization
5.query: SELECT ?obj ?o COUNT(DISTINCT ?x) AS ?archeologists WHERE { ?obj wdt:P31 wd:Q28171280. OPTIONAL{?x wdt:P101 ?obj; wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q3621491.} ?obj sc:name ?o. } GROUP BY ?obj ?o
output: history of ancient Israel and Judah

8.narrative: find for the ancient civilizations their deities
8.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?obj ?name ?dei ?dName WHERE { ?obj wdt:P31 wd:Q28171280. ?dei wdt:P279 wd:Q178885; wdt:P2596 ?obj. ?obj sc:name ?name. ?dei sc:name ?dName. }
SELECT DISTINCT ?obj ?name COUNT(DISTINCT ?div) as ?deity WHERE { ?obj wdt:P31 wd:Q28171280. ?dei wdt:P279 wd:Q178885; wdt:P2596 ?obj. ?div wdt:P31 ?dei. ?obj sc:name ?name. } GROUP BY ?obj ?name
